```

**Styling:** Rounded corners, custom accent color via CSS variable, minimalist design

---

### **3. Subscriptions Page**
**File:** `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/web/app/subscriptions/page.tsx`

Uses Checkbox component with sophisticated state management and selection logic:

```typescript
const [selectedIds, setSelectedIds] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set());

const toggleSelect = (id: string) => {
  setSelectedIds((prev) => {
    const next = new Set(prev);
    if (next.has(id)) next.delete(id);
    else next.add(id);
    return next;
  });
};

const toggleSelectAll = () => {
  if (isAllSelected) {
    setSelectedIds(new Set());
  } else {
    setSelectedIds(new Set(subscriptions.map((s) => s.id)));
  }
};

const toggleSelectChannel = (channelId: string) => {
  const channelSubs = grouped.get(channelId) ?? [];
  const channelSubIds = channelSubs.map((s) => s.id);
  const allSelected = channelSubIds.every((id) => selectedIds.has(id));
  // ... toggle logic
};
```

---

### **Styling Summary**

| Component | Type | Size | Shape | Color Scheme | Animation |
|-----------|------|------|-------|--------------|-----------|
| Switch | Radix UI | 8px×1.15rem (default) | Pill/Rounded | Primary checked / Input unchecked | `transition-transform` with translate-x |
| Switch (small) | Radix UI | 6px×3.5px | Pill/Rounded | Primary checked / Input unchecked | `transition-transform` |
| Checkbox | Radix UI | 4×4 (1rem) | Rounded square | Primary checked / Border input unchecked | `transition-shadow` |
| Native checkbox (rules) | HTML | 4×4 | Rounded square | Accent orange (#e8601a) | None |
| Native checkbox (table) | HTML | 4×4 | Rounded | Custom beacon accent var | None |
| Checkbox in label | UI | 4×4 | Rounded square | Primary on light | None |

---

### **Key Patterns Identified**

1. **Controlled State Management** - All toggles use React state with `checked` and `onCheckedChange`/`onChange`
2. **Label Association** - Checkboxes/switches always paired with labels in flex containers with gap spacing
3. **Toggle Functions** - Common pattern: `const toggleItem = (id) => setState(prev => prev.includes(id) ? prev.filter(...) : [...prev])`
4. **Batch Operations** - Select all/deselect all buttons with conditional text
5. **Styling Consistency** - Heavy use of Tailwind CSS with Radix UI data attributes for state styling
6. **Accessibility** - Proper label-input associations, focus-visible states, aria-invalid support
7. **Visual Feedback** - Focus rings, hover states, disabled opacity, smooth transitions

